# Nginx Reverse-Proxy Fix Guardrail

When user asks to solve Nginx issues, the agent MUST stay within this scope:

## Allowed Scope

- Nginx reverse-proxy config for:
  - `/console` dashboard static path passthrough to API
  - `/api/*` upstream proxy with prefix stripping
  - `/api/events/ws` WebSocket forwarding
  - `/api/events/stream` SSE forwarding with buffering disabled
- Supporting smoke/debug scripts and documentation for the above.

## Forbidden Scope

- MUST NOT change firmware.
- MUST NOT change unrelated backend business logic.
- MUST NOT refactor frontend structure unrelated to proxy pathing.
- MUST NOT modify OTA-only nginx template semantics except documenting separation.

## No-Drift Requirements

- Keep existing route contracts (`DASHBOARD_PATH=/console`, frontend `croc-api-base=/api`) intact.
- Prefer additive files/templates over risky rewrites of existing OTA config.
- Every fix part MUST include smoke checks and debug notes.

